<subSubSection id="C358655E861E6B38FAE28A60F8D5F9F2" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861E6B38FAE28A60F8D5F9F2" blockId="12.[1289,2272,1556,1917]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">
Australian Carboniferous species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861E6B38F7C48A60FA26F9F2" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" class="Gastropoda" family="Eotomariidae" genus="Eotomaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="umbilicata" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861E6B38F7C48A60FA26F9F2" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">Eotomaria umbilicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC861E6B38FA0D8A37F9BCF9F2" box="[1493,1574,1603,1641]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, from 'Marohn'.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E861E6B38FAE28A04F79FF8E6" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861E6B38FAE28A04F79FF8E6" blockId="12.[1289,2272,1556,1917]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861E6B38FA2E8A04F931F90C" authorityName="Ulrich &amp; Scofield" authorityYear="1897" box="[1526,1707,1648,1687]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eotomariidae" genus="Eotomaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861E6B38FA2E8A04F931F90C" box="[1526,1707,1648,1687]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">Eotomaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles somewhat 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861E6B38F7F28A04F9C3F95E" authority="de Koninck (1883)" authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1883" class="Gastropoda" family="Eotomariidae" genus="Mourlonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861E6B38F7F28A04F745F90C" box="[2090,2271,1648,1687]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">Mourlonia</emphasis>
de 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B24861E6B38FA9C8AEAF9C3F95E" author="Koninck, L. G. de" box="[1348,1625,1694,1733]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 240" refId="ref26509" refString="Koninck, L. G. de, 1883. Faune du calcaire Carbonifere de la Belgique. Gasteropodes. Musee Royal d'Histoire Naturelle de Belgique Annales 8: 1 - 240." type="journal article" year="1883">Koninck (1883)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in that 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861E6B38F8638AEAF7F5F95E" authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1883" box="[1979,2159,1694,1733]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eotomariidae" genus="Mourlonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861E6B38F8638AEAF7F5F95E" box="[1979,2159,1694,1733]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">Mourlonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a taller, more globular shell with minute umbilicus. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861E6B38FAD18A8EFA26F8BA" authorityName="Ulrich &amp; Scofield" authorityYear="1897" box="[1289,1468,1786,1825]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eotomariidae" genus="Eotomaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861E6B38FAD18A8EFA26F8BA" box="[1289,1468,1786,1825]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">Eotomaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously recorded as having the range from Ordovician to Silurian. If it is correctly placed, this record may extend to early Carboniferous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
